' @id(SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE) <<added>> this cycle (0021) — new sequence block
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-GOLIVE)
' Cycle 0021 diff (current side): SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE (the plan phase) now
' hands off to a new SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE block that manages auth, dry-runs,
' applies, provisions, migrates, and routes traffic — pausing only at
' irreversible steps and halting on first error. The CLI + LIVE Azure
' participants are new. Nothing removed.
title /mdd-deploy execution phase added · cycle 0021 diff (current)

actor "Operator" as Op
participant "/mdd-deploy\n(skill: plan + executor)" as Dep
participant "Bash: az, terraform, docker" as CLI <<added>>
participant "Azure subscription\n(LIVE)" as Az <<added>>

== SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE (RUN) — added cycle 0021 ==
Dep -> CLI : step 12 — az login + az account set (manage auth)
opt wrong/ambiguous subscription
  Dep -> Op : BLOCKING: surface mismatch; STOP
end
Dep -> CLI : step 13 — DRY-RUN (terraform plan / az what-if); show diff
Dep -> Op : step 14 — BLOCKING confirm "apply this plan?"\n(infra apply + secret writes + migration job)
Op --> Dep : approve
Dep -> CLI : apply; provision secrets; migrate; deploy revision at 0% traffic
CLI -> Az : provision + write secrets + schema migrate
opt any step failed
  Dep -> Op : HALT — report failing step; run NO further step
end
Dep -> Op : step 15 — GO-LIVE: surface full billing multi-factor gate; BLOCKING confirm
Op --> Dep : confirm go-live
Dep -> CLI : route 100% traffic (GO LIVE)
CLI -> Az : live-traffic cutover
Dep --> Op : step 16 — verify + report (LIVE, or HALTED)
@enduml
